in Mexico. Out of the nitty-gritty of "idian talk and interaction in Tijuana, Yeh captures the dynamics of desire and denial that permeate public spheres in our age of transnational crossings and fortified borders. Original and accessible, Passing is a timely work in light of current fierce debates over immigration, Latin American citizenship, and the US-Mexico border.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aMexico.  aTijuana.  aUS-Mexico border.  aborders.  aclass.  acollectivity.  amiddle class.  apublic sphere.  apublics.  apueblo.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311071193608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUrban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019z978311063851640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226512075423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226512075/original  a978-3-11-063851-6  Urban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019c2016d2019  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles